# Trivy suppressions — only for CVEs where the fix isn't actually available
# upstream. Each entry must come with a justification so a reviewer can tell
# the difference between "accepted risk" and "hiding the problem".

# CVE-2025-69720 — ncurses buffer overflow.
# Affects: libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin (Debian 13 / python:3.12-slim).
# Status: "affected" — Debian has not released a patched version yet.
# Risk: low for this app — the ncurses library is not exposed to untrusted
# input in the data-quality runner (no terminal UI in production).
# Revisit when: Debian publishes a fix in trixie security updates.
CVE-2025-69720
